Greater Albion Typefounders have just released four new faces on [Myfonts.com](http://web.archive.org/web/20131013102244/http:/new.myfonts.com/foundry/gatf/). These are:

- Sabinard, a distinctive modern Swash face;
- Coronard, A hybrid face with Blackletter astetics but Roman forms;
- Easter Fleurons, just as the name says, ornmaments for Easter; and
- Chapter Initials, Simple and Elegant initial caps, designed to compliment our Vertirna family.

Pop over to [Myfonts.com](http://web.archive.org/web/20131013102244/http:/new.myfonts.com/foundry/gatf/) and have a look. All feedback gratefully received.
